2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cLet not one of you mention anything bad to me about my companions, for I love to meet them while my heart is at peace.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 3896 Grade: Hasan (fair) according to Ahmad\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":5086,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/14\/no-jannah-until-islah\/","url_meta":{"origin":23310,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Grudges: Not admitted into Paradise until they reconcile","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 14, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe gates of Paradise are opened on Monday and Thursday. Allah forgives every servant who does not associate anything with Him, except a man with enmity between himself and his brother. It will be said: Delay\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":2122,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/03\/18\/tazkiyyah-al-nafs-qulub-hasad\/","url_meta":{"origin":23310,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Tazkiyyah: Pure hearts have no aggression, malice, envy","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 18, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Amr reported: We said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, who are the best of people?\u201d The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cOne with a heart swept clean and truthful in speech.\u201d We said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, we recognize truthful speech, but what is\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32207,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/16\/leaves-people-of-grudges\/","url_meta":{"origin":23310,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Hiqd: Allah leaves people of grudges to their malice","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 16, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Tha\u2019labah reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cOn the middle night of Sha'ban, Allah looks down upon His creation and He forgives the believers, gives respite to the unbelievers, and He abandons the people of malice to their malice until they give it up.\u201d Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33953,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/01\/27\/shafii-malice-forgiveness\/","url_meta":{"origin":23310,"position":5},"title":"Shafi\u2019i on Malice: Forgiveness relieved my soul of anxiety","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 27, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Shafi\u2019i, may Allah have mercy on him, wrote in his poetry, \u201cWhen I forgave and stopped holding malice against anyone, I relieved my soul of the worries of enmity.\u201d Source: Di\u0304wa\u0304n al-Sha\u0304fi\u02bbi\u0304 31 \u0642\u0627\u0644 \u0627\u0644\u0634\u0627\u0641\u0639\u064a \u0631\u062d